Detailed Description

MGGelPosition Container Class.

MGGelPositions is a class which constains MGGelPosition elements as a vector.

bool MGGelPositions::includes ( const MGGel *  gelin  )  const

Test if there is a MGGelPosition whose gel is the input gelin in this GelPositions' member.

If the gel of MGGelPosition is MGShell and gelin is MGFace, test is performed if the shell includes the face gelin as the shell constituent. Returns true if gelin is included in this MGGelPositions.

void MGGelPositions::push_back ( const MGGelPositions &  gelps  )  [inline]

void MGGelPositions::reset_with_symmetric_difference ( MGGelPositions &  pobjs2  ) 

replace this with symmetric_differecne of this and pobj, that is; (1) remove the same MGPickObject from this and pobjss.

(2) append the result pobjs2 to this. On return, pobjs2 will have null sequence.

MGGelPosition MGGelPositions::select_1st_curve (  )  const

Select the 1st MGCurve from this.

Function's return value is MGPickObject of MGCurve 1st encountered in this MGPickObject sequence. If this did not includes any MGCurve, null MGPickOjbect will be returned. This will be unchanged.

MGGelPosition MGGelPositions::select_1st_fsurface (  )  const

Select the 1st MGFSurface from this.

Function's return value is MGPickObject of MGFSurface 1st encountered in this MGPickObject sequence. If this did not includes any MGFSurface, null MGPickObject will be returned. This will be unchanged.

void MGGelPositions::select_curves ( MGGelPositions &  curves  )  const

Select all the MGCurve from this.

MGPickObject of MGCurve encountered in this MGPickObject sequence will be appended in curves. This will be unchanged.

void MGGelPositions::select_fsurfaces ( MGGelPositions &  surfaces  )  const

Select all the MGFSurface from this.

MGGelPositions of MGFSurface encountered in this MGPickObject sequence will be appended in surfaces. This will be unchanged.

bool MGGelPositions::symmetric ( const MGGelPositions &  gels2  )  const

Test if this is symmetric to gels2.

Symmetric means: (1) number of gels included is the same. (2) all of the gels are MGObject and they have the same manifold dimension.
